videos.description: So much for LSU's offense struggling as Danny Etling throws a pin-point accurate pass to the back of the end zone to D.J. Chark for the 37-yard score that gives the Tigers a 7-0 lead.
videos.headline: LSU airing it out for 37-yard touchdown

videos.description: Leonard Fournette is doing Fournette-like things, throwing a vicious stiff-arm to chuck a defender to the ground picking up the first down for LSU.
videos.headline: Fournette throws down defender with vicious stiff-arm

videos.description: Leonard Fournette run for 5 yds for a TD (Colby Delahoussaye KICK)
videos.headline: L. Fournette run for 5 yds for a TD, (C. Delahoussaye KICK)

videos.description: LSU's very own, Shaquille O'Neal visits his alma mater during college-football-mania and details how he has contributed to the Louisiana flood relief efforts and also shows off his brand new Hall of Fame ring.
videos.headline: Shaq beams with pride over alma mater and HOF ring

videos.description: Leonard Fournette gets plenty of blocking as he cuts through the line untouched before running over a final defender at the goal line to score and put LSU up 20-0 on Mississippi State.
videos.headline: No stopping Fournette as he finds the end zone from 25-yards out

videos.description: After struggling for most of the game, Mississippi State strikes back with two touchdowns in 40 seconds, this one a seven-yard TD pass to Fred Ross to cut the LSU lead to 23-20.
videos.headline: Mississippi State clawing back with another touchdown
